Electric-field instruments for heliophysics missions often utilize multiple receivers. This not only helps to accommodate the wide range of frequencies but also allows for different observation modes to be implemented. The simplest mode is waveform capture, in which a time series of voltage measurements from each antenna is recorded. This mode preserves the most information about E(t)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
