Magnetic reconnection refers to the rearrangement of the magnetic field in a highly-conducting fluid through resistive diffusion, which leads to a conversion of magnetic-field energy into particle energy. In regard to plasma turbulence, magnetic reconnection is a process that is closely related to intermittency. Intermittency is associated with localized large gradients in the magnetic field, which, according to AmpÃ¨reâs law in Eq.Â (23), corresponds to current sheets: localized regions of enhanced current j\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
